properties.name: DCI San Antonio - The Southwestern Championship
properties.description: Posted by Xmn07DCI Major Event Saturday, July 21, 2007 - Noon & 7 p.m. San Antonio, TX AlamodomeThe Southwestern Championship in San Antonio, Texas’ Alamodome, is an established site where legions of drum corps fans annually travel to see top corps in action during afternoon (prelims) and evening (finals) settings. Especially significant is that this will be one of the last opportunities to see most of the Division I corps head-to-head before they split routes on the tour, everyone meeting up again at the end of the season in Pasadena, Calif.

properties.name: Drums Along the Rockies
properties.description: Posted by Xmn07DCI Major Event Saturday, July 28, 2007 Denver, CO INVESCO Field at Mile HighMany of Drum Corps International’s finest corps will be at INVESCO Field at Mile High in Denver, Colo., as the stadium hosts the annual Drums Along the Rockies competition. The excitement level of the shows on the field is bound to soar as high as the peaks atop the nearby Rocky Mountains. From here, the DCI World Championship Finals is only two weeks and a handful of mountain tops away
